comment:
* Encrypted form of {@link android.adservices.topics.Topic}. This object will be used to return * encrypted topic cipher text along with necessary fields required to decrypt it. * *

Decryption of {@link EncryptedTopic#getEncryptedTopic()} should give json string for {@link * Topic}. Example of decrypted json string: {@code { "taxonomy_version": 5, "model_version": 2, * "topic_id": 10010 }} * *

Decryption of cipher text is expected to happen on the server with the corresponding algorithm * and private key for the public key {@link EncryptedTopic#getKeyIdentifier()}}. * *

Detailed steps on decryption can be found on Developer * Guide.

methods.name: public byte[] getEncryptedTopic()
methods.comment: Returns encrypted bytes for the JSON version of the {@link Topic} object as cipher text.

methods.name: public String getKeyIdentifier()
methods.comment: Returns key identifier for the used encryption key.

methods.name: public byte[] getEncapsulatedKey()
methods.comment: Returns the encapsulated key generated during HPKE setup.
